title: Grateful Dead Live at Giants Stadium on 1995-06-19
lineage: DAUD > Unknown Mics/Deck > DAT@48k > Soundforge 4.5a > CD Wave > SHN (seekable)
description: Cold Rain & Snow, Good Morning Little School Girl, Ramble On Rose, It's All Over Now, Lazy River Road, Me & My Uncle*-> Big River*, Don't Ease Me In Iko Iko, Unbroken Chain, Samba In The Rain, Corinna > Mathilda > Drums > Space > The Other One > Stella Blue, Throwin' Stones > Turn On Your Love Light E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Awful Wow...I knew this was bad when I saw it...but listening to it now....oy, what a mess.

Is Jerry even on stage? Listening to the Unbroken Chain (which is a better version that others, if a tad slow), I don't think he plays a single note...

Big River My second to last show ... I recall the Garcia having 'sound' trouble thru-out the 2nd set (Unbroken Chain). Since when is Big River the highlight? Am glad I made it to 6/30 before the End. This Aud is ok... I'll keep it because I was there, I hardly recommend this.

Wish I had missed it Old school Jersey is right. Seeing this show broke my heart, I wish I hadn't gone. For me the highlight was Samba in the Rain, need I say more? 
For a few years after this show I couldn't even listen to my old tapes. I sat through most of the show hoping Jerry was planning on rehab again when he got back to CA. I don't know if I even want to steam this show, never mind download it.
unbroken chain My 48th and last Dead show got my Unbroken Chain finally. Thanks Jerry
not the best, but still better than my sisters high school grad. (which I bailed on to attend this show)

Maybe it wasn't the greatest, but I had a blast anyway I sure remember the shows of 6-18 and 6-19-95. It was 102° outside and it sure took some of the energy out of everyone. The night wasn't much better inside the stadium, but I had fun anyway. I think after the first and hottest night of 6-18, I recall someone said they heard one of the band members say "Let's get the hell out of here.." as they were heading offstage for the evening. I remember thinking I don't blame them, as I had a migraine from the heat but tried to just have a great time anyway. 6-19 was better it seemed for everyone. These two dates were my last shows so they have a special place in that way for me.
